name: noaa-emergency-response-imagery
notes: The imagery posted on this site is in response to natural disasters. The aerial photography missions were conducted by the NOAA Remote Sensing Division. The majority of images were acquired from a nominal altitude of 7,500 feet, using a Trimble Digital Sensor System (DSS). The imagery GSD and coordinate system varies due to changing emergency response requirements.
